article.headline: East Tenn. St. 110, Campbell 96
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Tim Smith scored 37 points and Brad Nuckles chipped in 22 points and 15 rebounds to lead East Tennessee State to a 110-96 win over Campbell on Saturday. Smith shot 15-of-25 from the field, hitting three of his four 3-point attempts, and was perfect at 4-of-4 from the free throw line. He and Nuckles were among five players who scored in double figures for the Bucs (4-8, 2-2 Atlantic Sun), who are in their first season in the Atlantic Sun Conference. Courtney Pigram also had 15 points, Travis Strong added 14 and Ben Rhoda scored 12. Maurice Latham scored 16 points for the Camels (4-8, 3-2), who shot only 28.2 percent from the field in the first half -- compared to ETSU's 56.5 percent in the half -- to trail 65-38 at the break. Comerlee Poole added 15 points, Reggie Bishop had 14, Eric Smith scored 12 and Diego Aguiar had 10.
